headline: US Stock Market Today: S&P 500 Futures Edge Higher On Strong Jobs Data And Tariff Jitters
summary: The Morning Bull - US Market Morning Update Friday, Jan, 16 2026 US stock futures are pointing higher this morning, with E-mini S&P 500 contracts up about 0.3%, as investors weigh strong economic data against fresh trade tensions. Weekly initial jobless claims have dropped to 198,000, and continuing claims are at 1.884 million, numbers that signal a resilient job market and, for many households, better job security. headline: 3 Market-Beating Stocks to Target This Week
summary: Companies that consistently increase their sales, margins, or returns on capital are usually rewarded with the best returns, and those that can do all three for years on end are almost always the legendary stocks that return 100 times your money.
